		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> One year of top 16 decks.<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.97)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=12149'>Patrick "CaptCanada" Malboeuf</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=12149&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> August 17, 2003</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> 1-	I write this article mainly as a way to remember good Lotr moments and share my nostalgic smile with other veteran players.<br />
2-	Should you be only interested in useful Lotr information, you can always find an exclusive decklist of the deck I used day 2 of worlds to make top 8, as well as comments on other decks I used.<br />
3-	While some strangers will see this article as an arrogant piece of work, I hope that my friends and those who know me will see it as the expression of my grattitude towards them and towards the faith that allows me to continue to do well at this game.<br />
4-	It took me a while to collect all this information and to write this article and as such it is very possible that mistakes will have slipped by. Please excuse me for this.<br />
<br />
Ah! With DragonCon in a few weeks, I will celebrate one full year of Lotr ProTournaments. It has been a wild ride, from driving 24 hours sleeping 3 or 4 hours in the car in front of Wal Marts, to taking Mercedes cabs and playing people from all around the world, to making the road trip toVirginia with our fab four, stoping and laughing at evry possible fast food place, to taking a costly plane in the desert only to stay caged in my hotel when the marvels of the world are reproduced next street, to reproducing scenes from fast and furious at the expense of Pat’s car and heart rate, to watching rich grandads play squash while I discover that my agent’s arm is equivalent to that of a little school girl.<br />
<br />
Honestly, I look back at what Lotr pro gaming has allowed me to do and there was no way I would have predicted such a turn of events one year ago.<br />
<br />
And with the time for nostalgia comes the memories, and one of the things I find interesting looking back at are the pile of cards I used to win enough money to continue doing this passion of mine and to be able to play on day 2s of every event.<br />
<br />
So, if you’re interested, here are the decks Iused in big events in the past year and some comments to increase the nostalgia of how easier it was when you could just exert frodo to know how to win.<br />
<br />
