<br />
Between Worlds and Vegas, me and my brother spent countless hours play testing Two Towers  and our feeling was that the best free-peoples based deck was Help in doubt and need. Dom used it to go undefeated day 1 but it became obvious that all our play-testing had not higlighted the potency of Dunland. I can say my frist round matchup was disadvantaged, but looking up at all the choke/dunland deck I would have had to face in the later rounds, it was only fair that I took my poorly metaed deck and went to play in the team tournament. Back in the days of A Ranger’s versatility,  I  played Nazguls for a a good straight 6 months but over that period I think I got 3 or 4 shadow kill wins (and god knows I attended a lot of local tournaments). As Dom said after day one, when your shadow is Nazguls, you have to run like a madman. We spent all night between day 1 and 2 to think of another viable shadow, but couldn’t see that dunland was the right choice.<br />
<br />
<br />
