 <br />
The power of Wing-Chow! was revealed at Origins and because I feared that Josh would play mass condition removal on round one to beat my moria deck, I had to think of an alternative. Brochu and I sat down and designed this pile in about 3 minutes and were dancing like little girls afterwards. It was indeed a powerful fellowship but again, paired up with a shadow that doesn’t give any other choice than to run like a madman. The shadow was Pat’s conception and after doing so well on day 1 with it, I wasn’t one to argue at 3 in the morning. Still, I had to find a shadow that would allow me to play a balanced deck once more, like back in the Trust Me days, when your shadow could give you as much wins as your fellowship.<br />
<br />
